@startuml sequence-onboarding
' Sequence of the top-down invitation and onboarding chain (DataPilot v2).
' EY palette #3D108A #188CE5 #27ACAA #2DB757 #750E5C #2E2E38, accent #FFE600.
' No em or en dashes anywhere in the rendered text.

skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor white

skinparam sequence {
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #3D108A
  ParticipantFontColor white
  ParticipantBorderColor #2E2E38
  ParticipantFontSize 14
  ActorBackgroundColor #FFE600
  ActorBorderColor #2E2E38
  ActorFontColor #2E2E38
  ActorFontSize 14
  ArrowColor #2E2E38
  ArrowFontColor #2E2E38
  ArrowFontSize 13
  LifeLineBorderColor #2E2E38
  LifeLineBackgroundColor #E8E8EE
  GroupBorderColor #3D108A
  GroupFontColor #3D108A
  GroupHeaderFontColor white
  GroupBackgroundColor #3D108A
  DividerBackgroundColor #188CE5
  DividerFontColor white
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #FFFBD1
  BorderColor #2E2E38
  FontColor #2E2E38
  FontSize 13
}

actor "EY Admin (owner)" as EY
participant "Serverless API" as API #188CE5
participant "Supabase Auth" as AUTH #27ACAA
participant "Postgres (profiles)" as DB #2DB757
actor "Invited Super Admin" as INV

EY -> API : POST /api/invite with session token\n(email, function, bank name)
activate API
API -> DB : re-reads the caller's profile\n(role, bank, disabled flag)
DB --> API : caller = owner, rank 3, enabled
note right of API
  Server-side rank check: the invited role is
  fixed to invitableRole(caller), strictly one
  step down (owner to superadmin); any other
  requested role or a disabled caller is refused.
end note
API -> AUTH : inviteUserByEmail(email,\nmetadata: function, bank, department)
AUTH -> DB : trigger handle_new_user\ncreates the profile row
AUTH --> INV : invitation email with a link\nto /set-password
API -> DB : patch profile: role superadmin,\nbank name, department, invited_by lineage
DB --> API : profile complete
API --> EY : invitation confirmed
deactivate API

...

INV -> AUTH : follows the email link\n(session established from the link)
INV -> AUTH : chooses a password, nothing else\n(identity was set by the inviter)
INV -> DB : signs in and reads own profile\n(role, bank scope under RLS)
DB --> INV : per role landing redirect\n(admin tiers to /admin, analysts to Welcome)

note over EY, INV
  The chain repeats one rank down: the Super Admin invites Admins and the
  Admin invites Analysts; every invitee inherits the inviter's bank, and only
  the EY Admin (owner) ever names a bank, which creates the tenant.
end note
@enduml
